        Specified by:
        merge in interface Expression<T>
        Parameters:
        left - the preceding expression
        right - the following expression
        precedence - the precedence level being merged. Only expressions at this precedence level should be merged. Others should simply return the left expression, themselves and the right expression in that order.

      • defaultMerge

        protected List<Expression> defaultMerge(Expression left,
                                        Expression right)
        Base merge implementation. No merge is done, simply returns the left expression, this and the right expression.
        Parameters:
        left - the expression to the left of this expression
        right - the expression to the right of this expression
        Returns:
        a list containing the un-merged left expression, this and right expression
